<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-24T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-24T16:00:00-05:00" n="998" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d998">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.51/10–21444: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Dominican Republic</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Briggs</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Ciudad Trujillo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-24T16:00:00-05:00">October
                                    24, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 6:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>464. Referring to my telegram 331 July 13, 6 p.m.<note n="34" xml:id="d998fn34">Not printed.</note> I have been informed
                            confidentially by the representative of the holders of bonds of the
                            Dominican Republic that the Chase National Bank has agreed to make a
                            loan of $6,000,000 to the Dominican Government at 3½ percent. Inasmuch
                            as a budgetary surplus of $5,000,000 is anticipated for the present
                            fiscal year these two items would be approximately sufficient to provide
                            for the liquidation of the present outstanding balance of the foreign
                            debt.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Briggs</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>